  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to understand the differences in how patients with heart failure
      respond to exercise training compared to patients with heart failure and type 2 diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The investigators will measure exercise capacity in patients with heart failure or heart
      failure plus type 2 diabetes prior to and following a 12-week exercise training program
      (5d/wk, 30 min/d, 60-75% VO2max) to determine whether improvements in exercise capacity in
      response to exercise training are mitigated in patients with combined heart failure plus type
      2 diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
